        analyze:    "Lines L₁: 2x+3y=12, L₂: 3x−2y=6, L₃: 6x+9y=18 are given. Convert each to slope-intercept form. Determine all pairwise geometric relationships (parallel, perpendicular, coincident, or simply intersecting). Find all distinct intersection points. Determine whether L₁ and L₂ intersect on L₃.",
