        evaluate:   "A student applies the sine rule to a triangle where a = 9, b = 12, and angle A = 35°, finding sin B = 12 sin 35°/9 = 0.7648, and states that B = 49.9° is the only solution. Evaluate this — determine whether the student has correctly checked for the ambiguous case, calculate whether a second triangle is possible by testing B = 180° − 49.9°, and state the complete solution including both triangles if applicable.",
        create:     "Formulate a real-world problem set in a specific context (navigation, surveying, architecture, or sport — not generic 'triangle ABC') that requires applying the cosine rule to find a side, then the sine rule to find an angle, and finally Area = ½ab sin C to find an area. The numbers must be realistic for the chosen context. Provide a fully labelled diagram, complete worked solution with all steps justified, and a one-sentence interpretation of each calculated quantity in the real-world context."
