        apply:      "Solve completely: f(x) = x³ + x² − 10x + 8 = 0. First test rational root candidates, confirm one root using the Factor Theorem, perform synthetic division, and solve the depressed polynomial. State all roots and verify each by substitution.",
        analyze:    "A degree-4 polynomial f(x) has the following known information: f(1) = 0, f(−2) = 0, the leading coefficient is 2, and f has a y-intercept of 8. Deduce the multiplicity of each known root and write the complete factored form of f(x), verifying that the y-intercept condition is satisfied.",
        evaluate:   "A student attempts to solve x³ − 6x² + 11x − 6 = 0 by factoring directly as (x − 1)(x − 2)(x − 3) without showing any working. Evaluate this response — state whether the answer is correct, then demonstrate what working must be shown to earn full marks, including application of the Factor Theorem and synthetic division for at least two steps.",
        create:     "Construct a degree-3 polynomial equation that has one positive rational root, one negative rational root, and one root that is an irrational number. Show that your equation meets all three criteria by applying the Factor Theorem to verify the rational roots and using the quadratic formula (or completing the square) to find the irrational root. Sketch the graph, labelling all intercepts."
